# Network proxy required (machine in China)
This machine is located in mainland China. Any access to international resources must go through a proxy, otherwise commands may hang or time out.
## Default proxy setup
- macOS: `source /Users/yankay/scripts/proxy.sh`
- Linux: `source /root/proxy.sh` or `source ~/proxy.sh`
- Proxy variables (from proxy.sh):
  - `ALL_PROXY=socks5://10.6.108.200:10808`
  - `HTTP_PROXY=http://10.6.108.200:10809`
  - `HTTPS_PROXY=$HTTP_PROXY`
  - Lowercase variants are also set.
## When to apply
Before running commands that touch the public internet, enable proxy first, including (not limited to):
- `curl`, `wget`
- `git clone/fetch/push` — SSH remotes use `~/.ssh/config` `ProxyCommand` (SOCKS5); HTTPS remotes use `HTTPS_PROXY`.
- package managers: `apt`, `pip`, `uv`, `npm`, `yarn`, `pnpm`, `go`, `cargo`
- container tooling: `docker`, `containerd`, `nerdctl`, image pulls
If a command supports explicit proxy flags/config, prefer environment variables for consistency.
